    "summary": "--> Main interests and expertise: Justice in global health education and research, health equity (gezondheidsrechtvaardigheid), reciprocal North-South institutional collaborations, power dynamics and relationships between health professionals in LMICs (incl White Savior Industrial Complex and dialectical deafness), taking into account the role of personal and impersonal authority in hierarchical settings, also in historical perspective (colonial medicine, missionary medicine, tropical health, international health). And: Equitable/fair communication in international development and global health.\n\n--> Big fan of education for change: Challenge-Based Learning (CBL), Community-Engaged Learning (CEL), interdisciplinarity, intercultural competencies, Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), inclusive pedagogy, international internship support and Open Education projects (COIL: Collaborative Online International Learning).\n\n--> Big fan of applied research and translating results into use for actual change in global health\n\n--> Strong points: analytic, goal-oriented, writing",
